⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Karamazov Nature
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦The Karamazov Nature:BKZ:eac223⟧

WHO   — The Karamazov Nature — the broad heart
WHAT  — The novel's anthropology: human beings are wide enough to hold the ideal of the Madonna and the ideal of Sodom in one heart, and must choose.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Dostoevsky's whole vision is that we are not simple — that the same broad nature can murder a father or kiss the earth.
HOW   — By appetite, intensity, and a refusal of the lukewarm — the Karamazov is never merely moderate.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am broad — too broad; I hold the Madonna and Sodom in one heart, and the whole drama is which of them I will let win the house.

